today (Class Method) today method of DateTime class method today method of DateTime class
Returns a DateTime instance for the current day, with a time value of 00:00:00.000000.
&utc_offset_default_system;

fromEuropeanDate (Class Method) fromEuropeanDate method of DateTime class method fromEuropeanDate method of DateTime class
Returns a new DateTime object, created from a string in the format returned by the European option of the built-in function (dd/mm/yy). The time component will be set to 00:00:00.000000.
If specified, separator identifies the field separator character used in the string. The separator must be a single character or the null string (""). A slash ("/") is the default separator. The time component will be set to 00:00:00.000000. &utc_offset_default_system;

fromNormalDate (Class Method) fromNormalDate method of DateTime class method fromNormalDate method of DateTime class
Returns a new DateTime object, created from a string in the format returned by the Normal option of the built-in function (dd mon yyyy). The time component will be set to 00:00:00.000000.
If specified, separator identifies the field separator character used in the string. The separator must be a single character or the null string (""). A blank (" ") is the default separator. &utc_offset_default_system;

fromOrderedDate (Class Method) fromOrderedDate method of DateTime class method fromOrderedDate method of DateTime class
Returns a new DateTime object, created from a string in the format returned by the Ordered option of the built-in function (yy/mm/dd). The time component will be set to 00:00:00.000000.
If specified, separator identifies the field separator character used in the string. The separator must be a single character or the null string (""). A slash ("/") is the default separator. The time component will be set to 00:00:00.000000. &utc_offset_default_system;

fromStandardDate (Class Method) fromStandardDate method of DateTime class method fromStandardDate method of DateTime class
Returns a new DateTime object, created from a string in the format returned by the Standard option of the built-in function (yyyymmdd). The time component will be set to 00:00:00.000000.
If specified, separator identifies the field separator character used in the string. The separator must be a single character or the null string (""). A null string ("") is the default separator. &utc_offset_default_system;

fromUsaDate (Class Method) fromUsaDate method of DateTime class method fromUsaDate method of DateTime class
